dogecoin.text: @jeremysear I gave up on the institution long ago.

@jeremysear The thing about PR is it treats all views as valid and deserving of representation. The current system does too, I grant you, but since PR doesn't improve on that, it's largely just cosmetic. It's not *bad* as such, it's just not fixing anything broken.
@jeremysear I'm actually OK with conservatives having no representation, cheers.
@jeremysear You weren't. Because Michael McCormack sucks. If you'd had a different MP, such as a progressive, you'd have been represented fine.
@jeremysear Everyone does have a representative in parliament. It's just they're not very good.
@jeremysear And three or four they didn't.
@jeremysear You can't. You lost. It sucks. Welcome to being the left.
@jeremysear You can hold your MP to account now. They just won't listen which is why you need a better MP.

@jeremysear Agree. But that doesn't need PR. And in fact can't happen under PR because nobody will ever get a majority (well, rarely) so you'll have to move centrewise to govern. So nothing's accomplished.
@jeremysear Yes but Labor are very stupid.
@jeremysear Labor would work with the Liberals before the Greens again.

@jeremysear In 2010, under PR the result would have been a Labor/Green coalition, which is exactly what we got under IRV. In 2013, under PR, the Coalition would have won with support of Hanson. Which is exactly what we got. Etc.

@jeremysear Right, which demonstrates the parties are the problem, not the system. The result is the same. When you look at the maths, there's almost no election where the winner under HC would be substantively different.
@jeremysear meanwhile One Nation gets 10% of the vote and no seats and that's good.
@jeremysear By voting against them next time. Being disenfranchised and unrepresented is not the same as losing.
@jeremysear It does. You're just in the minority.
@jeremysear I live in a place run by Hare-Clark. It's fine, I guess, but you'd have to work hard to convince me it's made much of a sizable impact on the way government works.
@jeremysear Except then you get Tassie where Labor just straight up refuses to even deal with the Greens, rather than just move leftward to accommodate them.
@jeremysear No, I want the far-right to not have any influence no matter how many votes they get.
@jeremysear Sure, if you want the Libs and One Nation making decisions.
